title: Morgan Stanley Agreeing to Buy E*Trade for $13B
itunes:title: Morgan Stanley Agreeing to Buy E*Trade for $13B
description:
We get the Businessweek Agenda with Bloomberg Intelligence Chief Equity Strategist Gina Martin Adams and Bloomberg Stocks Editor Dave Wilson. Bloomberg Businessweek Deputy Editor Jim Aley and Bloomberg Green Editor Jillian Goodman share their insight on the crop software behind your daily cup of coffee. Bloomberg News Wall Street Reporter Sonali Basak walks through Morgan Stanley agreeing to buy discount brokerage firm E*Trade for $13 billion. And we Drive to the Close with Margie Patel, Senior Portfolio Manager at Wells Fargo Asset Management.

Hosts: Carol Massar and Jason Kelly. Producer: Doni Holloway. 

See omnystudio.com/listener for privacy information.
